ZCZC GE38
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 162300 UTC
DURING SATURDAY EVENING AND SUNDAY THE AZORES HIGH PRESSURE WILL EXTEND
A RIDGE ACROSS BISCAY AND FRANCE WHILE LOW PRESSURE 983 WILL BE CENTRED
IN THE NORWEGIAN SEA AND MIGRATES EWARDS THROUGH SUNDAY. EX-TROPICAL STORM
ERNESTO 1005 LOCATED IN SHANNON SATURDAY EVENING WILL ALSO MOV EWARDS ACROSS
THE UK ON SUNDAY AND FILL.
DURING MONDAY ANOTHER WEAK LOW PRESSURE AREA 1013 NW OF IRELAND AT FIRST
WILL TRAVERSE EWARDS ACROSS SCOTLAND TO LIE IN THE N SEA BY MIDNIGHT WHILST
A RIDGE BUILDS NWARDS FM THE AZORES HIGH TO THE W OF IRELAND. THIS RIDGE
WILL THEN MOV EWARDS ACROSS IRELAND AND BRITAIN THROUGH TUESDAY BEFORE BEING
FOLLOWED BY FURTHER TROUGHS OR WEAK LOW PRESSURE AREAS. WINDS WILL BE OCNL
STRG IN THE N SEA ON SATURDAY EVENING AND EARLY SUNDAY THEN MODERATING FOR
A TIME. OCNL STRG WINDS ARE FCST TO RETURN TO THE S LATJR SUNDAY THEN MODERATING
